<p><i><b>A Wrinkle in Time</b></i> is a <a href="/wiki/Science_fantasy" title="Science fantasy">science fantasy</a><sup id="cite_ref-Rock_0-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-Rock-0" title=""><span>[</span>1<span>]</span></a></sup> novel by <a href="/wiki/Madeleine_L%27Engle" title="Madeleine L'Engle">Madeleine L'Engle</a>, first published in 1962.<sup id="cite_ref-sqfish_1-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-sqfish-1" title=""><span>[</span>2<span>]</span></a></sup> The book won a <a href="/wiki/Newbery_Medal" title="Newbery Medal">Newbery Medal</a>, <a href="/wiki/Sequoyah_Book_Award" title="Sequoyah Book Award">Sequoyah Book Award</a>, and <a href="/wiki/Lewis_Carroll_Shelf_Award" title="Lewis Carroll Shelf Award">Lewis Carroll Shelf Award</a>, and was runner-up for the <a href="/wiki/Hans_Christian_Andersen" title="Hans Christian Andersen">Hans Christian Andersen</a> Award.<sup id="cite_ref-suncatcher_2-0" class="reference"><a href="#cite_note-suncatcher-2" title=""><span>[</span>3<span>]</span></a></sup> It is the first in L'Engle's <a href="/wiki/Time_Quartet" title="Time Quartet">series of books</a> about the Murry and O'Keefe families.</p>
